03/04/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The two-day meeting of defence ministers of countries participating in the Southeast Europe Co-operation Process (SEECP) concluded in Bucharest on Thursday (31 March) with a declaration vowing expanded collaboration in several areas. 
According to local media reports, the ministers agreed to intensify joint activities as regards destruction of surplus arms and ammunition, as well as social re-integration of staff laid-off as a result of military reforms. 
The participants decided on the establishment of three working groups, which would tackle problems related to such issues. 
(Fena - 01/04/05; Rompres - 31/03/05)
